

  COPOS

  - Cloud Of Points Of a Scanner


General Information
===================

COPOS is a software to control a webcam and transform it as a 3D scanner

The official web site is:
  http://copos.berlios.de/

The official download & development project site is:
  http://developer.berlios.de/project/showfiles.php?group_id=2163

Licensing
=========

COPOS is released under the terms of the GNU General Public License 
(GNU LGPL). 


Supported Platforms
===================

Currently COPOS supports

  * Linux with a webcam
      Tested under Linux


Requirements
============

  * GNU C compiler

  * GNU make

  * GTK 2.0 or later (http://www.gtk.org/)

  * OpenGL or Mesa (http://www.mesa3d.org/)

  * GTK-Doc (http://www.gtk.org/rdp/)  [optional]

  * GtkGLExt 1.0 or later


Installation
============

To build and install COPOS, type follows (use GNU make)

  $ ./configure --prefix=/foo/bar (other options...)
  $ make (or gmake)
  $ make install


Please read INSTALL or type "./configure --help" for more details.


Configure Options
=================

  --disable-pwc		disable Philips740K module compilation
  --include-pwc=DIR	pwc-ioctl.h is installed in DIR [default=/usr/src/linux/drivers/usb/media/]

Building the CVS Version of GtkGLExt
====================================

COPOS's Berlios CVS repository can be checked out through
anonymous (pserver) CVS with the following instruction set.
When prompted for a password for anonymous, simply press the Enter key. 

  $ cvs \
      -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.berlios.de:/cvsroot/copos \
      login
  $ cvs -z3 \
      -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.berlios.de:/cvsroot/copos \
      co copos

When you are at work on the CVS version of COPOS, you can use autogen.sh
for generating configure script and Makefiles.

  $ ./autogen.sh
  $ make
  $ make install

You may have to set ACLOCAL_FLAGS environment variable for some m4
macros used in configure.in.

The following versions of the GNU autotools are required.

  autoconf 2.x and above
  automake 1.4.x
  libtool  1.4


